President Trump recently announced new actions aimed at increasing quality, affordability, and fairness in the healthcare system. The initiative focuses on providing patients with information about healthcare costs and quality, empowering them to make informed decisions. The President emphasized the need for price transparency, as patients often face significant obstacles in finding the best care at the best price. The executive order signed by President Trump requires hospitals to publish prices that reflect what patients actually pay, making healthcare costs more clear and accessible. The order also aims to improve the quality of care by providing information about doctors and hospitals to help patients make better choices. The President highlighted the importance of giving patients the freedom to choose their doctors and treatments, while also lowering healthcare costs through increased competition. The executive order is part of a broader effort by the Trump administration to improve healthcare access and affordability for Americans.